<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1400,1325,1527]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,448,1325,1351]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bairae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,448,1325,1351]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Amblypsilopus bairae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[457,550,1326,1352]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is close to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vanschuytbroeck" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[690,793,1325,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavus">
<emphasis box="[690,793,1325,1352]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">A. flavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[855,1004,1325,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="friedmani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[855,1004,1325,1352]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">A. friedmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1013,1106,1326,1352]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in habitus. The last two species differ from 
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[423,534,1360,1387]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bairae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[423,534,1360,1387]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">A. bairae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[541,633,1361,1387]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the fore basitarsus at least two times as long as tibia and in a bifurcated cercus. Fore basitarsus 1.5 times as long as tibia in the new species; fore tibia and tarsus entirely covered with erect setulae, about as long as diameter of podomeres, somewhat longer at base of tibia and at base of basitarsus; cercus with broad and high basal part and long filiform distal part (
<figureCitation box="[198,325,1501,1527]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1926,1952]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,495,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-96@9.[189,1398,495,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 2. Amblypsilopus bairae sp. nov. Holotype, ♂ (SMNHTAU). A. Habitus. B. Head. C. Antenna. D. Fore tibia. E. Wing. F. Hypopygium, left lateral view, reflected light. G. Epandrial lobe, surstylus and base of cercus, lateral view, transmitted light." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4983310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4983310/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Fig. 2F–G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
